Miscellaneous Highlights: Over 17,000 spectators turned out at Jamaica’s National Stadium on Friday as the Reggae Boyz opened their 2024/2025 CONCACAF Nations League campaign against Cuba.
Others: The turnout was the highest since the Reggae Boyz’s 2019 clash with Honduras.
Jamaica earned a point in the match, which ended in a 0-0 draw.
The Reggae Boyz will face Honduras today (September 10, 2024), before returning to the National Stadium for a home game against Honduras on Monday, October 14, 2024.
